# Naming Conventions in Java

The coding rules followed by the programmer in writing Java programs are known as Naming Conventions.

(1) Packages
def:- packages are collection of "classess and interfaces".
rule:- packages must be in lower cavarse.

(2) Classes and Interfaces
def:- classes and Interfaces are collection of variables and methods.
rule:- The starting letter of every word in classes and Interfaces must be uppercase.

(3) Variables and Methods
def:- Variables are data holders.
      Methods are actions.
rule:- In variables and methods the first word must be lower case from second word onwards the first letter must be upper case.

(4) Keywords
def:- The pre-defined words from the lib are known as Keywords or Bulit-in words.
rule:- The keywords must be lower case.
